.TH "intel_guc_allocate_and_map_vma" 9 "intel_guc_allocate_and_map_vma" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
intel_guc_allocate_and_map_vma \- Allocate and map VMA for GuC usage
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" intel_guc_allocate_and_map_vma
.BI "(struct intel_guc *guc "  ","
.BI "u32 size "  ","
.BI "struct i915_vma **out_vma "  ","
.BI "void **out_vaddr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "guc" 12
the guc
.IP "size" 12
size of area to allocate (both virtual space and memory)
.IP "out_vma" 12
return variable for the allocated vma pointer
.IP "out_vaddr" 12
return variable for the obj mapping
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This wrapper calls \fBintel_guc_allocate_vma\fP and then maps the allocated
object with I915_MAP_WB.
.SH "RETURN"
0 if successful, a negative errno code otherwise.
